{"id":457,"parent_id":454,"book_id":1,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":457,"title":"Job 3","subtitle":"","short_title":"Job","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3","content":[["div",[".titleNumber","Chapter 3"],[".studySummary",["i","Job curses the circumstances of his birth—He asks, Why died I not from the womb?"]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.1","order":"02.19.003.33076"},["b","1"],"After this opened Job his mouth, and",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_1a"},"cursed"],"his day."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.2","order":"02.19.003.33077"},["b","2"],"And Job spake, and said,"],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.3","order":"02.19.003.33078"},["b","3"],"Let the day",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_3a"},"perish"],"wherein I was",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_3b"},"born"],", and the night",["i","in which"],"it was said, There is a man child conceived."],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.4","order":"02.19.003.33079"},["b","4"],"Let that day be darkness; let not God regard it from above, neither let the light shine upon it."],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.5","order":"02.19.003.33080"},["b","5"],"Let darkness and the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_5a"},"shadow of death"],"stain it; let a cloud dwell upon it; let the blackness of the day terrify it."],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.6","order":"02.19.003.33081"},["b","6"],["i","As for"],"that night, let darkness seize upon it; let it not be joined unto the days of the year, let it not come into the number of the months."],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.7","order":"02.19.003.33082"},["b","7"],"Lo, let that night be solitary, let no joyful voice come therein."],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.8","order":"02.19.003.33083"},["b","8"],"Let them curse it that curse the day, who are ready to raise up their mourning."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.9","order":"02.19.003.33084"},["b","9"],"Let the stars of the twilight thereof be dark; let it look for light, but",["i","have"],"none; neither let it see the dawning of the day:"],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.10","order":"02.19.003.33085"},["b","10"],"Because it shut not up the doors of my",["i","mother’s"],"womb, nor hid sorrow from mine eyes."],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.11","order":"02.19.003.33086"},["b","11"],"Why",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_11a"},"died"],"I not from the womb?",["i","why"],"did I",["i","not"],"give up the ghost when I came out of the belly?"],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.12","order":"02.19.003.33087"},["b","12"],"Why did the knees",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_12a"},"prevent"],"me? or why the breasts that I should suck?"],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.13","order":"02.19.003.33088"},["b","13"],"For now should I have lain still and been quiet, I should have slept: then had I been at rest,"],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.14","order":"02.19.003.33089"},["b","14"],"With kings and counsellors of the earth,",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_14a"},"which built desolate places"],"for themselves;"],["div",{"id":"15","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.15","order":"02.19.003.33090"},["b","15"],"Or with princes that had gold, who filled their houses with silver:"],["div",{"id":"16","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.16","order":"02.19.003.33091"},["b","16"],"Or as an hidden untimely birth I had not been; as infants",["i","which"],"never saw light."],["div",{"id":"17","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.17","order":"02.19.003.33092"},["b","17"],"There the wicked cease",["i","from"],"troubling; and there the weary be at",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_17a"},"rest"],"."],["div",{"id":"18","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.18","order":"02.19.003.33093"},["b","18"],["i","There"],"the prisoners rest together; they hear not the voice of the oppressor."],["div",{"id":"19","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.19","order":"02.19.003.33094"},["b","19"],"The small and great are there; and the servant",["i","is"],"free from his master."],["div",{"id":"20","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.20","order":"02.19.003.33095"},["b","20"],"Wherefore is",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_20a"},"light"],"given to him that is in",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_20b"},"misery"],", and life unto the bitter",["i","in"],"soul;"],["div",{"id":"21","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.21","order":"02.19.003.33096"},["b","21"],"Which long for",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_21a"},"death"],", but it",["i","cometh"],"not; and dig for it more than for hid treasures;"],["div",{"id":"22","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.22","order":"02.19.003.33097"},["b","22"],"Which rejoice exceedingly,",["i","and"],"are glad, when they can find the grave?"],["div",{"id":"23","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.23","order":"02.19.003.33098"},["b","23"],["i","Why is light given"],"to a man whose way is hid, and whom God hath hedged in?"],["div",{"id":"24","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.24","order":"02.19.003.33099"},["b","24"],"For my sighing cometh before I eat, and my roarings are poured out like the waters."],["div",{"id":"25","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.25","order":"02.19.003.33100"},["b","25"],"For the thing which I greatly feared is come upon me, and that which I was afraid of is come unto me."],["div",{"id":"26","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.26","order":"02.19.003.33101"},["b","26"],"I was not in safety, neither had I rest, neither was I quiet; yet trouble came."]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"1a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.1a","order":"02.19.003.33102"},["b","1a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/curse"},"TG Curse"],"."],["div",{"id":"3a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.3a","order":"02.19.003.33104"},["b","3a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/despair"},"TG Despair"],"."],["div",{"id":"3b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.3b","order":"02.19.003.33106"},["b","3b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/20.14.14-18"},"Jer. 20:14 (14–18)"],"."],["div",{"id":"5a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.5a","order":"02.19.003.33108"},["b","5a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/23.4"},"Ps. 23:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/44.19"},"44:19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/107.14.10,14"},"107:14 (10, 14)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/57.10"},"D&C 57:10"],"."],["div",{"id":"11a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.11a","order":"02.19.003.33110"},["b","11a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/job/10.18.18-19"},"Job 10:18 (18–19)"],"."],["div",{"id":"12a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.12a","order":"02.19.003.33112"},["b","12a"],["span.small","HEB"],"receive."],["div",{"id":"14a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.14a","order":"02.19.003.33114"},["b","14a"],["span.small","HEB"],"who rebuilt ruins."],["div",{"id":"17a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.17a","order":"02.19.003.33116"},["b","17a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/paradise"},"TG Paradise"],"."],["div",{"id":"20a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.20a","order":"02.19.003.33118"},["b","20a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.67"},"D&C 88:67"],"."],["div",{"id":"20b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.20b","order":"02.19.003.33120"},["b","20b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/122.7.1-7"},"D&C 122:7 (1–7)"],".",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/suffering"},"TG Suffering"],"."],["div",{"id":"21a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/job/3.21a","order":"02.19.003.33122"},["b","21a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/9.6"},"Rev. 9:6"],"."]]}
